{"title":"Specialized Levo SL gets Genie Shock Upgrade","link":"https://bikerumor.com/specialized-levo-sl-emtb-with-genie-shock/","date":1725997721000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/2024-specialized-levo-sl-alloy-genie-shock-eMTB-1-1536x1152.webp\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" alt=\"closeup of alloy specialized levo sl eMTB with new genie shock.\" /></p>\n<p>Introduced on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/specialized-stumpjumper-15-redefines-trail-bike-capability-w-genie-rear-shocks-adjustable-geo/\">the latest Stumpjumper</a>, the Specialized Levo SL lightweight e-mountain bike now comes with their Genie rear shock for improved small bump compliance without giving up big hit support.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Basically, it’s two already-launched products combined to make a better bike. The <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/specialized-turbo-levo-sl-gen-2-mixed-wheel-size-e-bike-emtb/\">2nd gen Levo SL</a> launched in May 2023 and is one of the lightest trail eMTBs on the market. It’s also a solid performer (<a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/specialized-turbo-levo-sl-gen-2-review/\">read our review here</a>) with 150mm travel and 160mm forks paired with a well-tuned and user-adjustable Horst Link suspension.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Specialized-fox-genie-shock-cutaway-view-jpg.webp\"><img width=\"2500\" height=\"1847\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Specialized-fox-genie-shock-cutaway-view-jpg.webp\" alt=\"castaway view of specialized fox genie air shock with two-stage air chamber.\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Specialized-fox-genie-shock-cutaway-view-jpg.webp 2500w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Specialized-fox-genie-shock-cutaway-view-297x219.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Specialized-fox-genie-shock-cutaway-view-1536x1135.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Specialized-fox-genie-shock-cutaway-view-120x89.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Specialized-fox-genie-shock-cutaway-view-768x567.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Specialized-fox-genie-shock-cutaway-view-2048x1513.webp 2048w\" /></a><figcaption>Note the active air volume in blue and how it loses access to the extra chamber in the outer sleeve once the piston passes 70% of its stroke.</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, it’s getting the Genie shock, co-developed with Fox, which uses a two-stage air chamber that’s higher volume for the first part of the stroke, then gets smaller in the last 30% of travel to ramp up more quickly to prevent bottom out.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/2024-specialized-levo-sl-e-mountain-bike-family-jpg.webp\"><img width=\"2500\" height=\"1669\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/2024-specialized-levo-sl-e-mountain-bike-family-jpg.webp\" alt=\"all models of specialized levo sl lightweight e-mountain bike.\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/2024-specialized-levo-sl-e-mountain-bike-family-jpg.webp 2500w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/2024-specialized-levo-sl-e-mountain-bike-family-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/2024-specialized-levo-sl-e-mountain-bike-family-1536x1025.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/2024-specialized-levo-sl-e-mountain-bike-family-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/2024-specialized-levo-sl-e-mountain-bike-family-768x513.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/2024-specialized-levo-sl-e-mountain-bike-family-2048x1367.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/2024-specialized-levo-sl-e-mountain-bike-family-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/2024-specialized-levo-sl-e-mountain-bike-family-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Levo SL gets Genie shocks across the entire range (complete bike prices from $7,000 to $14,000 with alloy and carbon frame options), except for the coil shock-equipped Ohlins edition ($11,000).</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.specialized.com/us/en/shop/bikes/electric-bikes/electric-mountain-bikes/turbo-levo?productfamily=Turbo+Levo+SL\" target=\"_blank\">Specialized.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/specialized-levo-sl-emtb-with-genie-shock/\">Specialized Levo SL gets Genie Shock Upgrade</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"7f72f74794e864f4aec6e6a1d6db4b4858236a8f1ebe6ebc43d9e6a70b2ca2bc","category":"Cycling"}